Chiefdom of Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey
thumb | 300px | right | chiefdoms Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey The cacique of Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey (cacicazgo Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey) spanned the entire southeast of Hispaniola, bordered to the north by the cacique of Magu&lt;U+00E1&gt; and the Bay Samana, south by the Caribbean, east by the Canal de la Mona, and west by the cacique of Maguana and Magu&lt;U+00E1&gt;. This cacique only covered the territories of the current Dominican Republic.
It was ruled by the cacique Cayacoa. Its headquarters was located in present-day Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey. This cacique extended from Cabo Enga&lt;U+00F1&gt;o to the river Haina. It was divided into 21 nita&lt;U+00ED&gt;nos. This cacique is also known as the Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;anamo.
The mother goddess of Hig&lt;U+00FC&gt;ey was Atabeira, which means &quot;Mother of the original stone&quot;.
